….Dismisses Noah Noah’s Petition for lack of Merit. The House of Assembly Election Petition Tribunal sitting in Uyo, the Akwa Ibom State Capital has affirmed the victory of the Leader ,Akwa Ibom State House of Assembly, Rt Hon. Sir Udo Kierian Akpan and the Peoples Democratic Party as the winner of the March 9, 2019 general elections. The Petitioner Noah Noah and the All Progressive Congress (APC) has filled a petition challenging the result of the March 9th House of Assembly election that saw the re-election of Rt Hon (Sir) Udo Kierian Akpan as the Member representing Oruk Anam in Akwa Ibom State House of Assembly. The Petitioner who was absent in court had prayed the tribunal to set aside the result of March 9th Oruk Anam State Constituency election due to irregularities and criminal activities; and declare him the rightful winner of the election. In delivering judgement, the tribunal  noted that the prayers of Noah Noah to declare him winner of the March 9th election was invalid and inconsistent due to his Submission that the election was marred by violence and irregularities. The tribunal wonders why the Petitioner was interested in claiming victory of an election that was marred by violence and irregularities as indicated in his written address. The tribunal noted that the petitioner’s petition was poorly written, inconsistent, and wanting in merit. The tribunal maintained that the petition lack substance, credible evidence and has violated the mandatory standard of election petition as outlined in the electoral act, thus the petition was struck out. The court urges the petitioner to pay N150,000 fine. Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook 